Integration Testing Plan 
Hospital Management System (HMS)
1. Purpose
This integration testing plan verifies that the backend services
and clinical modules of the Hospital Management System work together
correctly. The goal is to ensure seamless data exchange, reliable workflows,
and accurate clinical operations across all connected services.
 

2. Scope
The integration testing covers interactions between:
* Authentication Service
* User Management Service
* Patient Management Service
* Appointment Service
* Electronic Medical Records (EMR) Service
* Clinical Service
* Laboratory Service
* Pharmacy Service
* Billing Service
* Notification Service
* Reporting Service
* Database Layer
* External APIs (if applicable)
 

3. Testing Objectives
* Verify communication between backend services.
* Ensure patient information flows correctly across modules.
* Validate clinical workflows from patient registration to discharge.
* Confirm data consistency across services and databases.
* Detect interface and communication errors.
* Verify security, authentication, and authorization mechanisms.
 

4. Test Environment
Environment Requirements
Component	Description
Backend API	Development/Staging Environment
Database	MySQL/PostgreSQL
Authentication	JWT/OAuth
API Testing Tool	Postman/Insomnia
Test Framework	Jest, Mocha, PyTest, or equivalent
CI/CD	GitHub Actions/GitLab CI
Logging	ELK Stack or Application Logs
 

5. Integration Testing Strategy
Approach
A combination of:
* Top-Down Integration Testing
* Bottom-Up Integration Testing
* API Integration Testing
* End-to-End Workflow Testing
will be used to validate interactions between modules.
Test Execution Order
1. Authentication Services
2. User Management
3. Patient Management
4. Appointment Scheduling
5. Clinical Services
6. Laboratory Services
7. Pharmacy Services
8. Billing Services
9. Notifications
10. Reporting
 

6. Integration Test Scenarios
6.1 Authentication → Clinical Services
Objective: Verify authenticated clinicians can access clinical functions.
Test Cases
* Login with valid credentials.
* Access patient records after authentication.
* Verify token validation.
* Verify unauthorized access is blocked.
Expected Result
* Authenticated users gain access according to role permissions.
 

6.2 Patient Registration → Clinical Service
Objective: Verify newly registered patients are available to clinical staff.
Test Cases
* Register patient.
* Retrieve patient in clinical module.
* Update patient information.
* Verify synchronization.
Expected Result
* Clinical service displays accurate patient data.
 

6.3 Appointment Service → Clinical Service
Objective: Verify appointments are accessible during consultations.
Test Cases
* Create appointment.
* Check appointment availability in clinician dashboard.
* Start consultation.
* Complete consultation.
Expected Result
* Appointment information appears correctly within clinical workflow.
 

6.4 Clinical Service → EMR Service
Objective: Verify clinical notes are stored in patient records.
Test Cases
* Record diagnosis.
* Record vital signs.
* Save treatment plan.
* Retrieve medical history.
Expected Result
* EMR updates successfully with consultation details.
 

6.5 Clinical Service → Laboratory Service
Objective: Verify laboratory requests are transmitted correctly.
Test Cases
* Create lab request.
* Receive request in laboratory module.
* Update test status.
* Return results.
Expected Result
* Laboratory results become available in patient records.
 

6.6 Clinical Service → Pharmacy Service
Objective: Verify prescriptions are transferred correctly.
Test Cases
* Create prescription.
* Pharmacy receives prescription.
* Dispense medication.
* Update medication status.
Expected Result
* Prescription workflow completes successfully.
 

6.7 Clinical Service → Billing Service
Objective: Verify bill generation after consultation.
Test Cases
* Complete consultation.
* Generate billing entry.
* Add laboratory charges.
* Add medication charges.
Expected Result
* Accurate bill generated automatically.
 

6.8 Billing Service → Notification Service
Objective: Verify billing notifications are sent.
Test Cases
* Generate invoice.
* Trigger notification.
* Verify email/SMS delivery.
Expected Result
* Patient receives billing notification.
 

6.9 Laboratory Service → EMR Service
Objective: Verify lab results are attached to patient records.
Test Cases
* Complete laboratory test.
* Upload result.
* Retrieve result in EMR.
Expected Result
* Results appear in patient medical history.
 

6.10 Pharmacy Service → Inventory Service
Objective: Verify medication dispensing updates inventory.
Test Cases
* Dispense medication.
* Check stock reduction.
* Generate low-stock alert.
Expected Result
* Inventory reflects current stock levels.
 

7. Data Validation Testing
Verify:
* Patient IDs remain consistent across services.
* Medical records are linked correctly.
* Appointment references are valid.
* Billing entries match clinical activities.
* Laboratory results belong to correct patients.
 

8. Error Handling Tests
Scenarios
* Database unavailable.
* Service timeout.
* Invalid patient ID.
* Expired authentication token.
* Duplicate patient records.
* Network interruption.
Expected Results
* Meaningful error messages returned.
* No data corruption.
* Failed transactions rolled back where necessary.
 

9. Security Testing
Verify:
* JWT authentication.
* Role-based access control (RBAC).
* Secure API endpoints.
* Audit logging.
* Data encryption in transit (HTTPS).
* Protection against unauthorized access.
 

10. Performance Testing
Metrics
* API response time < 2 seconds.
* Concurrent users supported as specified.
* Database queries optimized.
* No memory leaks during prolonged usage.
Scenarios
* Multiple simultaneous consultations.
* High appointment booking volume.
* Bulk laboratory result uploads.
 

11. Entry Criteria
* All backend services deployed.
* APIs available.
* Database configured.
* Test data prepared.
* Authentication service operational.
 

12. Exit Criteria
* All critical integration tests passed.
* No high-severity defects open.
* Clinical workflows validated successfully.
* Security and performance requirements met.
 

13. Deliverables
* Integration Test Cases
* Test Execution Reports
* Defect Reports
* Test Summary Report
* Integration Test Sign-Off Document
 

14. Conclusion
This integration testing plan ensures that all backend
and clinical services of the Hospital Management System communicate effectively,
maintain data consistency, support complete patient-care workflows, and meet the 
required security, reliability, and performance standards before deployment.
